title: I prompted myself!
body:
Song: When I come around – Green Day

Character: Kaminari Denki in an alternative universe with no quirks

It’s not that he always feels worthless. It’s probably because he’s had way too many beers for feelings to be considered alright anymore.

Denki stretches lazily on the floor, his back arching into his bed, making his spine tingle with a little pain.

He’s in the limbo between about to be dumped or staying together ‘cause they’re all they’ve got, and it’s painful. So painful that Kaminari downs another beer, hoping this one will be the one to finally make him pass out.

He doesn’t regret anything, even when he can hear them on the other side of the wall, crying because things aren’t alright. He’s in half a mind to walk out and try and make them feel better, try to soothe the horrible loneliness that comes with the situation, but he feels useless and knows it’s partly his fault anyway.

And he doesn’t want to hear the accusing tone in which they’ll tell him what he’s already heard before, and what he should do to fix his life.

Maybe it’s better to break up if there’s no happy ending to whatever they have anyway.

The blond scrambles onto his bed and closes his eyes, thinking they know where to find him if he needs it when sleep finally takes him.
